Package: riskyr
Type: Package
Title: A toolbox for teaching and training risk literacy more transparently
Version: 0.0.0.904
Date: 2018-01-05
Authors@R: c(person("Hansjoerg", "Neth", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                     email = "h.neth@uni.kn"),
              person("Felix", "Gaisbauer", role = "aut"),
              person("Nico", "Gradwohl", role = "aut"))
Author: Hansjoerg Neth [aut, cre],
  Felix Gaisbauer [aut],
  Nico Gradwohl [aut]
AuthorUrl: http://neth.de
Maintainer: Hansjoerg Neth <h.neth@uni.kn>
Description: Provides a set of basic risk literacy tools in R.
    Starting with a condition (e.g., a disease), a corresponding decision (e.g., based on a clinical judgment or diagnostic test), 
    and basic probabilities (prevalence, sensitivity, specificity) we provide a range of metrics and alternative representations of 
    probabilities and frequencies (for a population of N individuals). By offering a variety of perspectives on the interplay 
    between these parameters, riskyr renders teaching and training of risk literacy more transparent. 
